verbose_text: Eligible subjects were men or women aged between 18 and 85 years, with SUA levels of> 7.0 mg/dl with a history of gout, SUA levels of> = 8.0 mg/dl with complications (defined as a need for pharmacologic or other treatment for lithangiuria, hypertension, hyperlipidemia, or abnormal glucose tolerance) or SUA levels of> = 9.0 mg/dl without complications.
